Breaking News Man found guilty in 2013 Delray double homicide Dutch eventing draws 60,000 spectators Horse inspector Alain James of France, center rear, notes his observations during an inspection prior to the dressage event of the Military Boekelo, Netherlands, Wednesday, Oct. 7, 2015. More than 60,000 spectators enjoyed a day of Olympic-standard equestrian competition when they attended the Military Boekelo, one of the biggest sporting events held in the Netherlands. Eventing competition consists of dressage, cross-country and show jumping and competitors were seeking a spot at the Rio Olympics at the picturesque competition held near the city of Enschede.
